1448 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[download_plugin]: get version of settings's type, " << sub_iter.value();
1449 }
1450 else if (boost::iequals(sub_iter.key(), "version")) {
1451 version = *(Semver::parse(sub_iter.value()));
1452 }
1453 else if (boost::iequals(sub_iter.key(), "description")) {
1454 description = sub_iter.value();
1455 }
1456 else if (boost::iequals(sub_iter.key(), "url")) {
1457 url = sub_iter.value();
1458 }
1459 }
1460 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[download_plugin 1]: get type " << type << ", version " << version.to_string() << ", url " << url;
1461 download_url = url;
1462 }
1463 }
1464 }
1465 else {
1466 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[download_plugin 1]: get version of plugin failed, body=" << body;
1467 }
1468 }
1469 catch (...) {
1470 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << "[download_plugin 1]: catch unknown exception";
1471 ;
1472 }
1473 }).on_error(
1474 [&result, &err_msg](std::string body, std::string error, unsigned int status) {
1475 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << "[download_plugin 1] on_error: " << error<<", body = " << body;
1476 err_msg += "[download_plugin 1] on_error: " + error + ", body = " + body;
1477 result = -1;
1478 }).perform_sync();
1479
1480 bool cancel = false;
1481 if (result < 0) {
1482 j["result"] = "failed";
1483 j["error_msg"] = err_msg;
1484 if (m_agent) {
1485 m_agent->track_event("networkplugin_download", j.dump());
1486 }
1487 if (pro_fn) pro_fn(InstallStatusDownloadFailed, 0, cancel);
1488 return result;
1489 }
1490
1491
1492 if (download_url.empty()) {
1493 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[download_plugin 1]: no available plugin found for this app version: " << SLIC3R_VERSION;
1494 if (pro_fn) pro_fn(InstallStatusDownloadFailed, 0, cancel);
1495 j["result"] = "failed";
1496 j["error_msg"] = "[download_plugin 1]: no available plugin found for this app version: " + std::string(SLIC3R_VERSION);
1497 if (m_agent) {
1498 m_agent->track_event("networkplugin_download", j.dump());
1499 }
1500 return -1;
1501 }
1502 else if (pro_fn) {
1503 pro_fn(InstallStatusNormal, 5, cancel);
1504 }
1505
1506 if (m_networking_cancel_update || cancel) {
1507 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << boost::format("[download_plugin 1]: %1%, cancelled by user") % __LINE__;
1508 j["result"] = "failed";
1509 j["error_msg"] = (boost::format("[download_plugin 1]: %1%, cancelled by user") % __LINE__).str();
1510 if (m_agent) {
1511 m_agent->track_event("networkplugin_download", j.dump());
1512 }
1513 return -1;
1514 }
1515 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[download_plugin] get_url = " << download_url;
1516
1517 // download
1518 Slic3r::Http http = Slic3r::Http::get(download_url);
1519 int reported_percent = 0;
1520 http.on_progress(
1521 [this, &pro_fn, cancel_fn, &result, &reported_percent, &err_msg](Slic3r::Http::Progress progress, bool& cancel) {
1522 int percent = 0;
1523 if (progress.dltotal != 0)
1524 percent = progress.dlnow * 50 / progress.dltotal;
1525 bool was_cancel = false;
1526 if (pro_fn && ((percent - reported_percent) >= 10)) {
1527 pro_fn(InstallStatusNormal, percent, was_cancel);
1528 reported_percent = percent;
1529 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[download_plugin 2] progress: " << reported_percent;
1530 }
1531 cancel = m_networking_cancel_update || was_cancel;
1532 if (cancel_fn)
1533 if (cancel_fn())
1534 cancel = true;
1535
1536 if (cancel) {
1537 err_msg += "[download_plugin] cancel";
1538 result = -1;
1539 }
1540 })
1541 .on_complete([&pro_fn, tmp_path, target_file_path](std::string body, unsigned status) {
1542 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[download_plugin 2] completed";
1543 bool cancel = false;
1544 int percent = 0;
1545 fs::fstream file(tmp_path, std::ios::out | std::ios::binary | std::ios::trunc);
1546 file.write(body.c_str(), body.size());
1547 file.close();
1548 fs::rename(tmp_path, target_file_path);
1549 if (pro_fn) pro_fn(InstallStatusDownloadCompleted, 80, cancel);
1550 })
1551 .on_error([&pro_fn, &result, &err_msg](std::string body, std::string error, unsigned int status) {
1552 bool cancel = false;
1553 if (pro_fn) pro_fn(InstallStatusDownloadFailed, 0, cancel);
1554 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << "[download_plugin 2] on_error: " << error<<", body = " << body;
1555 err_msg += "[download_plugin 2] on_error: " + error + ", body = " + body;
1556 result = -1;
1557 });
1558 http.perform_sync();
1559 j["result"] = result < 0 ? "failed" : "success";
1560 j["error_msg"] = err_msg;
1561 if (m_agent) {
1562 m_agent->track_event("networkplugin_download", j.dump());
1563 }
1564 return result;
1565}

2010 // Windows : "C:\Users\username\AppData\Roaming\Slic3r" or "C:\Documents and Settings\username\Application Data\Slic3r"
2011 // Mac : "~/Library/Application Support/Slic3r"
2012
2013 if (data_dir().empty()) {
2014 boost::filesystem::path data_dir_path;
2015 #ifndef __linux__
2016 std::string data_dir = wxStandardPaths::Get().GetUserDataDir().ToUTF8().data();
2017 //BBS create folder if not exists
2018 data_dir_path = boost::filesystem::path(data_dir);
2019 set_data_dir(data_dir);
2020 #else
2021 // Since version 2.3, config dir on Linux is in ${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}.
2022 // https://github.com/prusa3d/PrusaSlicer/issues/2911
2023 wxString dir;
2024 if (! wxGetEnv(wxS("XDG_CONFIG_HOME"), &dir) || dir.empty() )
2025 dir = wxFileName::GetHomeDir() + wxS("/.config");
2026 set_data_dir((dir + "/" + GetAppName()).ToUTF8().data());
2027 data_dir_path = boost::filesystem::path(data_dir());
2028 #endif
2029 if (!boost::filesystem::exists(data_dir_path)){
2030 auto older_data_dir = data_dir_path.parent_path() / "BambuStudio-SoftFever";
2031 if(boost::filesystem::exists(older_data_dir)){
2032 copy_directory_recursively(older_data_dir,data_dir_path);
2033 boost::system::error_code ec;
2034 boost::filesystem::rename(data_dir_path / "BambuStudio.conf", data_dir_path / "OrcaSlicer.conf", ec);
2035 boost::filesystem::rename(data_dir_path / "BambuStudio.conf.bak", data_dir_path / "OrcaSlicer.conf.bak", ec);
2036 }
2037 else
2038 boost::filesystem::create_directory(data_dir_path);
2039 }
2040 } else {
2041 m_datadir_redefined = true;
2042 }
2043
2044 // start log here
2045 std::time_t t = std::time(0);
2046 std::tm * now_time = std::localtime(&t);
2047 std::stringstream buf;
2048 buf << std::put_time(now_time, "debug_%a_%b_%d_%H_%M_%S_");
2049 buf << get_current_pid() << ".log";
2050 std::string log_filename = buf.str();
2051#if !BBL_RELEASE_TO_PUBLIC
2052 set_log_path_and_level(log_filename, 5);
2053#else
2054 set_log_path_and_level(log_filename, 3);
2055#endif
2056
2057 //BBS: remove GCodeViewer as seperate APP logic
2058 if (!app_config)
2059 app_config = new AppConfig();
2060 //app_config = new AppConfig(is_editor() ? AppConfig::EAppMode::Editor : AppConfig::EAppMode::GCodeViewer);
2061
2062 // load settings
2063 m_app_conf_exists = app_config->exists();
2064 if (m_app_conf_exists) {
2065 std::string error = app_config->load();
2066 if (!error.empty()) {
2067 // Error while parsing config file. We'll customize the error message and rethrow to be displayed.
2068 throw Slic3r::RuntimeError(
2069 _u8L("OrcaSlicer configuration file may be corrupted and is not abled to be parsed."
2070 "Please delete the file and try again.") +
2071 "\n\n" + app_config->config_path() + "\n\n" + error);
2072 }
2073 // Save orig_version here, so its empty if no app_config existed before this run.
2074 m_last_config_version = app_config->orig_version();//parse_semver_from_ini(app_config->config_path());
2075 }
2076 else {
2077#ifdef _WIN32
2078 // update associate files from registry information
2079 if (is_associate_files(L"3mf")) {
2080 app_config->set("associate_3mf", "true");
2081 }
2082 if (is_associate_files(L"stl")) {
2083 app_config->set("associate_stl", "true");
2084 }
2085 if (is_associate_files(L"step") && is_associate_files(L"stp")) {

2089 }

1629 fs::remove(dest_path);
1630 mz_bool res = mz_zip_reader_extract_to_file(&archive, stat.m_file_index, dest_zip_file.c_str(), 0);
1631 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << __FUNCTION__ << boost::format(", extract %1% from plugin zip %2%\n") % dest_file % stat.m_filename;
1632 if (res == 0) {
1633 mz_zip_error zip_error = mz_zip_get_last_error(&archive);
1634 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << "[install_plugin]Archive read error:" << mz_zip_get_error_string(zip_error) << std::endl;
1635 close_zip_reader(&archive);
1636 if (pro_fn) {
1637 pro_fn(InstallStatusUnzipFailed, 0, cancel);
1638 }
1639 return InstallStatusUnzipFailed;
1640 }
1641 else {
1642 if (pro_fn) {
1643 pro_fn(InstallStatusNormal, 50 + i/num_entries, cancel);
1644 }
1645 try {
1646 auto backup_path = boost::filesystem::path(backup_folder.string() + "/" + dest_file);
1647 if (fs::exists(backup_path))
1648 fs::remove(backup_path);
1649 std::string error_message;
1650 CopyFileResult cfr = copy_file(dest_path.string(), backup_path.string(), error_message, false);
1651 if (cfr != CopyFileResult::SUCCESS) {
1652 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << "Copying to backup failed(" << cfr << "): " << error_message;
1653 }
1654 }
1655 catch (const std::exception& e)
1656 {
1657 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << "Copying to backup failed: " << e.what();
1658 //continue
1659 }
1660 }
1661 }
1662 catch (const std::exception& e)
1663 {
1664 // ensure the zip archive is closed and rethrow the exception
1665 close_zip_reader(&archive);
1666 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << "[install_plugin]Archive read exception:"<<e.what();
1667 if (pro_fn) {
1668 pro_fn(InstallStatusUnzipFailed, 0, cancel);
1669 }
1670 return InstallStatusUnzipFailed;
1671 }
1672 }
1673 }
1674 else {
1675 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(error) << boost::format("[install_plugin]: %1%, mz_zip_reader_file_stat for file %2% failed")%__LINE__%i;
1676 }
1677 }
1678
1679 close_zip_reader(&archive);
1680
1681 if (pro_fn)
1682 pro_fn(InstallStatusInstallCompleted, 100, cancel);
1683 if (name == "plugins")
1684 app_config->set_str("app", "installed_networking", "1");
1685 BOOST_LOG_TRIVIAL(info) << "[install_plugin] success";
1686 return 0;
1687}

3861{

3863

3865 std::string error;

3870 if (j.contains("code")) {
3871 if (!j["code"].is_null())
3872 code = j["code"].get<int>();

3884 if (msg_dlg.ShowModal() == wxOK) {

3886 }

3896 return;
3897 }

◆ select_language()

bool Slic3r::GUI::GUI_App::select_language ( )
private
4726{
4727 wxArrayString translations = wxTranslations::Get()->GetAvailableTranslations(SLIC3R_APP_KEY);
4728 std::vector<const wxLanguageInfo*> language_infos;
4729 language_infos.emplace_back(wxLocale::GetLanguageInfo(wxLANGUAGE_ENGLISH));
4730 for (size_t i = 0; i < translations.GetCount(); ++ i) {
4731 const wxLanguageInfo *langinfo = wxLocale::FindLanguageInfo(translations[i]);
4732 if (langinfo != nullptr)
4733 language_infos.emplace_back(langinfo);
4734 }
4735 sort_remove_duplicates(language_infos);
4736 std::sort(language_infos.begin(), language_infos.end(), [](const wxLanguageInfo* l, const wxLanguageInfo* r) { return l->Description < r->Description; });
4737
4738 wxArrayString names;
4739 names.Alloc(language_infos.size());
4740
4741 // Some valid language should be selected since the application start up.
4742 const wxLanguage current_language = wxLanguage(m_wxLocale->GetLanguage());
4743 int init_selection = -1;
4744 int init_selection_alt = -1;
4745 int init_selection_default = -1;
4746 for (size_t i = 0; i < language_infos.size(); ++ i) {
4747 if (wxLanguage(language_infos[i]->Language) == current_language)
4748 // The dictionary matches the active language and country.
4749 init_selection = i;
4750 else if ((language_infos[i]->CanonicalName.BeforeFirst('_') == m_wxLocale->GetCanonicalName().BeforeFirst('_')) ||
4751 // if the active language is Slovak, mark the Czech language as active.
4752 (language_infos[i]->CanonicalName.BeforeFirst('_') == "cs" && m_wxLocale->GetCanonicalName().BeforeFirst('_') == "sk"))
4753 // The dictionary matches the active language, it does not necessarily match the country.
4754 init_selection_alt = i;
4755 if (language_infos[i]->CanonicalName.BeforeFirst('_') == "en")
4756 // This will be the default selection if the active language does not match any dictionary.
4757 init_selection_default = i;
4758 names.Add(language_infos[i]->Description);
4759 }
4760 if (init_selection == -1)
4761 // This is the dictionary matching the active language.
4762 init_selection = init_selection_alt;
4763 if (init_selection != -1)
4764 // This is the language to highlight in the choice dialog initially.
4765 init_selection_default = init_selection;
4766
4767 const long index = GetSingleChoiceIndex(_L("Select the language"), _L("Language"), names, init_selection_default);
4768 // Try to load a new language.
4769 if (index != -1 && (init_selection == -1 || init_selection != index)) {
4770 const wxLanguageInfo *new_language_info = language_infos[index];
4771 if (this->load_language(new_language_info->CanonicalName, false)) {
4772 // Save language at application config.
4773 // Which language to save as the selected dictionary language?
4774 // 1) Hopefully the language set to wxTranslations by this->load_language(), but that API is weird and we don't want to rely on its
4775 // stability in the future:
4776 // wxTranslations::Get()->GetBestTranslation(SLIC3R_APP_KEY, wxLANGUAGE_ENGLISH);
4777 // 2) Current locale language may not match the dictionary name, see GH issue #3901
4778 // m_wxLocale->GetCanonicalName()
4779 // 3) new_language_info->CanonicalName is a safe bet. It points to a valid dictionary name.
4780 app_config->set("language", new_language_info->CanonicalName.ToUTF8().data());
4781 return true;
4782 }
4783 }
4784
4785 return false;
4786}
